data.description: Here’s your chance to own a Country Colonial on a 7 acre, private, scenic piece of property in the Downingtown School District!  Be sure to click on the virtual tour link or ask your agent to send it to you.   Opportunities for private parcels like this do not come along often.  Take the scenic Dowlin Forge one way street in along the river, then head up the private drive to 4 Dowlin Forge.  There are only 5 homes on this quiet, private and scenic street.  Pull into the circular driveway and step out into the peaceful setting that this home sits upon.  This 4 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom Colonial could use a little updating but has great bones.  The HVAC is new in 2022, the rooms are all decently sized, and the floors don’t have a bow or a squeak in them!  This home is built solid on a cinderblock foundation.  The kitchen is an open layout with an island, solid wood Country cabinets and stainless steel appliances. The hall bathroom upstairs has been freshly remodeled.  There is a finished basement with plenty of storage downstairs.  The home has an oversized 2 car garage and a shed.  Walk the property to enjoy all of the views and nature surround.  Located near Marsh Creek State Park hiking and biking trails.  Fishing, horseback riding, volley ball courts and Shamona Park are right down the street.  You can hike or bike right into Downingtown on the Struble Trail.  The home is also located near the Eagleview restaurants the Brandywine River, public Transportation, the PA turnpike and within the award winning Downingtown School District and highly rated STEM Academy.  Schedule your showing now!
